            <div class="text-info">The Arsenal Arena stadium is a football stadium in Shchaslyve (Kiev region), in the past it was the home arena of the Knyazha football club, now Arsenal Kyiv. Opened on October 13, 2007 as part of the infrastructure of the educational complex. It accommodates 1 000 spectators, seats for individual seats.


The stadium was opened on October 13, 2007 with the support of "Knyazha". The first match at the new stadium was a game between the veterans of Dynamo Kiev and the veterans of the football team of the village of Shchaslyve. Next to the stadium was built a 9-storey rehabilitation and fitness complex and an indoor arena with artificial cover.

Until 2009, the stadium was the home scene of the Knyazha football club, which played here first, second and then the first league matches. In the spring of 2013, the Bila Tserkva "Arsenal" played several fights on the "Princess Arena". Since 2014, home-based matches at Shchaslyve are held by Kyiv's Arsenal, and since 2015, the players of the stadium have also become youth squadrons of Donetsk Shakhtar.</div>

